<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,152,327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,263,289]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
This name is derived from the Spanish “agalla” (gall) and Greek “myia” (fly). It is considered feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
